What is variable ?
Variable in Postman is a reusable placeholder (key-value pair) that stores values you can reference throughout your request, collections, environments, and scripts.

Why is variable used?
In short, Postman variables are used to automate updates and keep your data organized. Instead of manually typing a URL or token 50times, you type it once and let the variable handle the rest.

Where are variable used?
You can plug a variable into almost any part of the Postman interface using the {{variable_name}}

ŌĆó	Request URL : {{base_url}}/users/1
ŌĆó	Headers: Key: Authorization, Value: Bearer{{my_token}}
