Local Variable
These variables we can create at request level. But in the request level we donŌĆÖt find variable section. So, we need to write a script under pre-request script.
There is no direct method for this. We need a proper script.

How to create a variable script for request level
1>open the postman
2>select the request
3>click on pre-request script
4>add the below script
//local variables
pm.variables.set("url_local", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");
5>now come to get and type below url
{{url_local}}/rest/api/2/issue/CAT-2
6>Click on send

Till now we have created the variable at different level like global, environment and collection.

Now let see how to create all the level at the request level.

Use the below scripts under the pre-request script

//Global variables
pm.globals.set("userid_global", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");

//Environment variables
pm.environment.set("T2", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");

//Collection variables
pm.collectionVariables.set("url2_collect", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");

Unset /remove the created variables.

Requirement is once the variable is created under request and the once the request is executed the created variable should get delete it should be created permanently.

1>go to postman
2>select the script
3>click on post request
4>now add the below script to delete the variable
//Global variables
pm.globals.unset("userid_global", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");

//Environment variables
pm.environment.unset("T2", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");

//Collection variables
pm.collectionVariables.unset("url2_collect", "https://jira-jdc-t2.devtools.intel.com");


